The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Geoff to coach Pune side
                                                                                                                       7                                      Geoff to coach Pune side
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The newly formed IPL team Sahara Pune Warriors appointed former Australian opener Geoff Marsh as the chief coach of the team with former England all rounder Dermot Reeve as his deputy, according to a media release issued by the franchisee.         
	We are delighted that we have been able to hand the reins of the team to two of the ablest professionals in the field. Geoff, with his wealth of experience and knowledge will be the captain of the ship while Dermot with his aggressive approach, enthusiasm and experience will assist him, team boss Subrata Roy Sahara told the mediapersons in Lucknow on Monday.         
	Marsh, who has guided Australia to World Cup triumph in 1999 and also coached Zimbabwe was thrilled with the appointment.         
	The IPL is the most exciting thing to happen to world cricket and Sahara Pune Warriors is in turn the most exciting thing to happen to IPL. I am extremely excited about this opportunity, said Marsh who has opened in 50 Test matches and 117 ODIs for Australia.                                                                                                                     
